public abstract class PrototypeHelper<T extends SmugObjectData<T>>
extends java.lang.Object

Author:
Anton Spaans. This is a helper class for objects implementing ISmugObjectPrototype and ISmugObject. Do not call any of its methods directly.

postUpdate

public static <T extends SmugObjectData<T>> T postUpdate(T smugObject)
This method should not be called directly. Called after an Update or Refresh. It makes sure that the Smugmug object is in sync with the Smugmug repository.

postDelete

public static <T extends SmugObjectData<T>> void postDelete(T smugObject)
This method should not be called directly. Called after a Delete. It makes sure that the Smugmug object is deleted from the cache and that its ID is cleared.

get

public T get(int ID)
                                throws SmugmugException
This method implements the ISmugObjectPrototype.get(ID) for (almost) all types of Smugmug objects. It calls 'getAll()' to make sure all the objects of type T are fetched from the Smugmug repository (or cache) and returns the one with the given ID.

Parameters:
ID - The ID of the Smugmug object (of type T) to retrieve.
Returns:
The desired Smugmug object.
Throws:
SmugmugException
